Sugarbear Spring Pop Up!
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come celebrate spring with Sugarbear! The weather is getting warmer, it's officially ice cream season, and we've been using the extra daylight to bring you some all new flavors! Try our brand new Root Beer ice cream, its like a root beer float all in a scoop. Or there's our refreshing and floral Lavender Matcha, as green as Bernal Hill. If chocolate is more your thing, you've got to try Double Dark Chocolate, super-rich and made with a double dose of Callebaut dark chocolate. Finally, due to popular demand we're bringing back an old favorite, our delicious Horchata ice cream. Swing by Mateo's for a well-deserved dessert and try them all!
Saturday, March 26, 2016, 6 PM - 10 PM in PDT
Mateo's Taqueria

Cathy Segal-Garcia & The Moment…Live Recording @ The BlueWhale
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
A great musical friendship between like minds and old friends. Jazz meets funk, abstract & ethereal. Veteran art chick leads a jazzy outing that flies under the radar in left field. A subtle yet captivating feel that transcends the normal expectations of jazz. Come join us for a live recording of The Moment @ The Blue Whale Monday, June 18th, 2012 9:00 pm to 12:00 am CATHY SEGAL-GARCIA vocal JEFF RICHMAN guitar GARY FUKUSHIMA keyboard CHUCK MANNING sax BRAD DUTZ percussion KIO GRIFFITH visuals

Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come celebrate the end of your week at Causes. Our world-famous Happy Hour is back for one week and ONE WEEK ONLY in November and it should not be missed. You know the drill: some boozing, some schmoozing, scrumptious snacks, creepy mustaches, beer pong, sunset strolls on the balcony and much, much, MUCH more. Everyone is welcome to invite a few guests, so feel free to round up friends, siblings, parents, roommates, spouses, lovers and pets. Please RSVP to this event so we have an accurate headcount. Look forward to seeing everyone soon!

CATHY APPEARS @ TUESDAY NITE JAZZ @ THE JOINT
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Cathy appears tomorrow night at Jazz @ The Joint!!!!!!!!!!!!!! A new series on the west side of L.A. on Tuesday nites! ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ April 3rd ...Two groups for the price of one! at 9:15 Vocalist Cathy Segal-Garcia's latest group of cool and jazz-funky players..Playing lots of originals, and jazz standards done in a unique way, in the way that only Cathy and these guys can do! Jeff RIchman on guitar Gary Fukushima on keyboard Brad Dutz on percussion Chuck Manning on sax. PLUS!!! Spoken Word Interludes by Michael C. Ford And, at 8:00 ...( the son of Brad Dutz) Jaspur Dutz on sax and his group... "Izanami" featuring: Luca Ferrara: Guitar Jeremy Corren: Piano Sarah Kuo: Bass The Joint is located at 8771 W. Pico Blvd. in the first block east of Robertson Blvd. ... Los Angeles 90035 Online reservations accepted and suggested. Go to www.thejointlive.com and go to "Contact" and just fill out the form. $10 cover ... $10 minimum -- food or drink. Our Menu is very nice, appetizers, salads, entrees...between $5 and $17, and regular bar, including specialty drinks! Parking: There's street parking, parking across the street behind Walgreens, and a marked public parking lot on Pico Blvd. before the Robertson intersection on the same side of street as The Joint (the north side)

Thrive East Bay | Liberation | Sunday, Dec 6th
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Join Thrive East Bay on Sunday, Dec 6th as we explore the theme and practices of Liberation. Thrive East Bay is a purpose-driven community for people of all ages and backgrounds committed to transforming our lives, communities, and world. We are creating a new kind of community that is informed by modern science and ancient wisdom, infused with a deep sense of purpose and interconnectedness, and focused on social change. We welcome all people as we journey toward personal growth, shared learning, and collective action. What: Thrive East Bay Sunday events provide an opportunity to connect with a diverse and inspiring group of people, be uplifted by music, singing, and poetry, and to experience the transformative power of community in service to a world that works for all. When: Sunday, Dec 6th from 10:30am - 12:30pm (please arrive on time!) Where: Oakstop in downtown Oakland 1721 Broadway #201 Oakland, CA 94612 (right next to the 19th Street Bart station) Theme: Liberation Co-Hosts: Elli Nagai-Rothe & Joshua Gorman Song Leaders: the Thrive East Bay Choir Speaker: Akaya Windwood, President of the Rockwood Leadership Institute Cost: You are invited to contribute whatever you feel called to and are able to. To help us cover our costs, we suggest a contribution of $15 - $30. No one will be turned away for lack of funds. RSVP: Please RSVP at the Tickets link above if you're able to attend. You are welcome to invite your family and friends. Please keep in mind that we are building an intentionally diverse community of people from many races, sexual preferences, gender identities, physical abilities, income ranges, and ages. Childcare: Please bring your little ones! Reservations for childcare are required so we can plan accordingly, so please let us If you would like a spot for your child or children at thriveeastbay@gmail.com. Volunteers: We are seeking volunteers to help with the set-up and break-down of this event. If you are available to arrive early or stay late, please let us know at thriveeastbay@gmail.com. We are a new community looking to build connections with those who are called to the intersections of love, liberation, and the celebration of Life. Please join us! In partnership, the Thrive East Bay Team
Sunday, December 6, 2015, 10:30 AM - 12:30 PM in PST
Oakstop

Hot Tub Chess Club #3: Simultaneous Exhibition + "How To Beat Your Dad At Chess"
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Join the Bay Area's hottest new chess club for our third event at the always-steamy Archimedes Banya. *** TICKETS: http://bit.ly/HotTubChessClubJan2016 *** - $25 Early Bird tix are now SOLD OUT. - We have a limited number of $30 Discount Presales available (20% off). Once these are gone the regular price is $37. All presale ticketholders get discounted banya passes and one free beverage. *** SCHEDULE *** 6-7pm: Chess Club Sauna Social Hour. Come mingle with the chess clubbers in the big communal Russian sauna. The resident chess master will be on hand to answer all of your burning questions about chess, saunas, and life. (Please exercise caution if asking for life advice — your results may vary.) 7-7:30pm: Simultaneous Exhibition. Chess master Jordy Mont-Reynaud will take on all challengers, using no more than 5 seconds per move. Score a draw and win a free beverage; beat the master to win a free banya pass! 7:30-8pm: All Levels Class — "How To Beat Your Dad At Chess". Jordy will explain the fundamentals of chess strategy and tactics. His signature teaching method focuses on pattern recognition — helping you to see the board like a master. It's the quickest way to pick up the skills you need to turn the tables on your chess arch-nemesis — whether that's your Dad, your coworker, or that one annoying friend who always beats you. 8pm till closing: Free play. Blitz, bughouse, strip chess, etc. We've got 5 brand new digital clocks ready to go. You can even use our brand new Floating Chessboard to dominate your friends and impress your date, all without leaving the comfort of your hot tub or pool. *** NEW: VIP TICKETS *** Each VIP ticket includes 60m of personalized chess instruction for you + 1 guest. Lessons begin with one game of blitz chess (for evaluation purposes) followed by 50m of personalized instruction. *** HOSTS *** JORDY MONT-REYNAUD (chessmaster in residence) Jordy became the youngest ever chess master in the United States at age 10. He was ranked #2 in the world at age 10 and #1 in the U.S. at age 16. He earned his B.S. in Symbolic Systems from Stanford (2004) and then did a bunch of startups. Current projects include Omies and Mindgames. ARCHIMEDES BANYA (www.banyasf.com) Archimedes Banya is where cultures of the world meet to bring you a unique bathing experience. The banya is a remarkable blend of 'past and present', where ancient traditions of Greek laconica, Turkish hammam, German thermen, Russian banya combine with science and technology to create an experience like no other. Detoxing in perfectly heated rooms, plunging into an ice-cold pool, enjoying a breathtaking view on a sun-lit deck, conversing over a delicious meal - you can have it all in a quintessentially San Francisco style.
Thursday, January 7, 2016, 7 PM - 10 PM in PST
Archimedes Banya
